'''Boti falls''' is a twin [[waterfall]] located at Boti in [[Manya Krobo]] in the [[Eastern Region, Ghana|Eastern Region]] of [[Ghana]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Boti falls|url=http://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/tourism/boti_falls.php|publisher=[[GhanaWeb]]|accessdate=2 May 2014}}</ref>  These twin falls are referred to as female and male.

== Location ==
It is located 17km North-east of [[Koforidua]], which is the eastern regional capital. It is just over 30 minutes drive from [[Koforidua]] and over 90 minutes from [[Accra]] depending on the means of transportation<ref>{{cite web|title=How to get there|url=http://www.dearghana.com/attractions/boti-falls/|website=www.DearGhana.com|publisher=DearGhana|accessdate=1 February 2015}}</ref>

